			<h3>Final Product</h3>
			<p class="project-description">I began by parsing the individual entries and creating a local JSON object to keep track of unique words within a given entry.
			</p>
			<br>
			<p class="project-description">Then I compared this JSON object with the database to check if any of the words in this entry already existed in the database. If they did, I would mark the JSON object as a word with a match and then in a later function increase the count for that word. If any of the words in the new entry didn't already exist in the database I would mark them as a non-matched word and then I would create a new database entry in a later function.
			</p>
			

